Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With their gesture, they wish to express their support for their country ' s nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
Students began praying Tuesday at noon at the facility and then chanted death slogans to the US and Israel.
Several hundred university students trained on Tuesday in the Iranian city of Isfahan human shields around the nuclear technology center where uranium is worked.
They intend to demonstrate their willingness to defend their country's nuclear programme with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, according to all indications, is striving to achieve nuclear weapons.
In Israel there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began praying at noon before the nuclear facilities in Isfahan and then launched death slogans against the US and Israel.
