In Need for Speed: The Run competes throughout America.
Overview
A journey, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper oversights of a routine journey during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which The Run is added, raised high expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old race series Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again.
We also feel curious to know how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As usually happens in NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total computation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, we cannot and cannot call ourselves mistakes, but rather the incomprehensible disillusionment of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
That way, you don't even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries in the series.
So, it's nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that diminishes visibility.
In the mountains, however, care must be taken not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to get ahead of a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to buy time (timed classic tooth) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than would be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action is well suited to this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, so good.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, collisions are no longer the same.
Of games of this type you cannot be expected to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by doing a very tight run or running the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can make you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five available resets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the start.
So it's just a help in case something doesn't go well, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, even resetting does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage from memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or stop.
It's the same when you arrive, because it's programmed because the "surprise" will always happen right under your nose.
The adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, you will always be overtaken by the same opponent in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front of you, so at first you can mush the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it surely disappoints you right away.
And it's a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that boredom doesn't fit, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be attentive to the petrol pumps next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight motorways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the upper level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with background for the profile.
At the same time, there is an online Autolog feature, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community functions available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you start to run in darkness along the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and suddenly from behind comes the convoy of the metro and takes you just ahead.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the game programming no one even thought a little or whether the authors actually take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore rather confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game isn't over.
The fun is assured, but get ready because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The Carolina University choirs will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Students' Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During this event, twenty chorales from high school and university centers will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has high participation in festival".
Among the current choirs are the chorale of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee there is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of Czech jazzist Karel Ričička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velvet" will be held at the venues of celebration of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university chorales, including the chorus of the Uninversity Carolina, will participate.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Day of Students with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows by students and morning concerts.
Further information can be found on the festival page www.festacademica.cz
