ADB Urges Asia to Help Rescue the Eurozone
The Asian Development Bank (ADB) has called on India and China to prepare to help rescue the eurozone from its sovereign debt crisis to avoid a long-term recession that would prevent the growth of Asian economies.
Rajat Nag, Managing Director of the Manila-based Asian Development Bank, said the world's two largest fastest growing economies had to "do everything possible" to accelerate the recovery of the economic bloc either through the International Monetary Fund or directly through bilateral agreements.
He warned against BRIC [Brazil, Russia, India, China] countries that observe Europe's difficulties in a "impartial" way and said that Asian financial assistance along with European leadership and resources would help prevent a long-term crisis in the global economy.
"We're all in this together."
