Lee Howell, Managing Director of the World Economic Forum, also wondered why India's reserves should be used to keep the many well-paid Greek public sector workers, in jobs of poorly managed companies, and loss-making companies such as railways.
Mr. Nag said the eurozone crisis threatens "significant chain effects" across Asia.
The Asian Development Bank's forecast of 7.5 percent economic growth in Asia for 2011/12 now faces "downside risks" due to Europe's threat.
He said vulnerable emerging markets needed to make "contingency plans" to protect themselves from a crisis and significant capital outflows from their economies.
Serious Pentagon warnings about possible defense cuts
Defense Secretary Leon Panetta warmed up Congress on Monday, warning that the upcoming automatic budget cuts could undermine national security and provoke a chain financial reaction from the Pentagon corridors, to the battlefields of Afghanistan, to civilian assembly chains.
