We all love each other and we love creating music.
We're lucky to go to places in the world we always wanted to go.
Things couldn't be better for us.
What did it mean for you to have been a fundamental part of the grunge's emergence?
It's always been an honor to be part of that big band.
We are very close friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It's surprising when a movement comes from a group of friends and it's unusual.
From time to time, a band emerges from a city, but it is much stranger when five or ten bands leave the same city at the same time.
We are proud and honored to be part of the Seattle group.
We still play with some of them from time to time.
Last year, we were at a festival with Alice in Chains and we were in Canada with Mudhoney, we saw Soundgarden on his tour, so we're lucky to be friends with all of them yet and we're honored to be part of that Seattle sound that came up.
It is also very strange that a band like yours stays together and with the same members for so long.
Yes, four of us have been together for 21 years and Matt (Cameron) joined us 13 years ago, which alone is much longer than many bands last.
First, I think we are all fortunate to be still alive and, second, we all care about others.
We are all very close friends and, thanks to that, musical avenues have also opened that give everyone freedom to experience.
We trust each other with each other's music and it couldn't be better.
Your relationship with the word fame has not been simple; however, thanks to your success, you have been able to do whatever you want.
How do you find a balance sheet?
As we have grown, it has been easier to find a balance sheet.
We make sure we're not too much touring because it's easy to fall into that game of the big crowds and the people who love your music.
As long as you remember that people are there for the music, that reminds you that you must respect the music and what brought it, without being infatuated by being famous and being a rock star, something that none of us really care about.
How do you remember your other Mother Love Bone project?
I think we wrote very good songs and at first it was a great thing.
We were a band for almost three years and never released a record until after Andy (Andrew Woods) died.
There were a lot of frustrations because it lasted so long and the most important thing is that we are still very close friends of Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore), who started in the band with us and when I hear a song or see a photo I think about the amazing person Andy was and how he made me laugh, it was always a pleasure to go to work, laugh, talk about music and football and much more.
He was a surprising human being and we missed him.
The national band Las Robertas will be in charge of opening the show in Costa Rica.
Is it true that you know her work, especially Eddie Vedder, and that's why you chose her for the opening?
Yes, the production sent us videos with various proposals and that was the band we liked the most, so we are eager to see what Las Robertas can offer live and must be very entertaining.
Why do they always change the lyrics of Yellow Ledbetter live?
That's a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), so I don't know.
He sings it and I think he does it with the first thing he can think of.
As a bass player, what are your influences?
There's so many of them.
Among the first ones I can think of are Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many that I could talk all afternoon about bass players that I love.
How has Pearl Jam managed to keep the grunge relevant even though it is no longer a fashion?
I think all of us always feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think about her, she reminds me of the bands I mentioned before, like Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those that came up at the same time, and, if there's relevance now, I think it's a wonderful thing because it's music that's worth listening to and bands like Mudhoney are now making better music than ever.
At first, his music had darker content and has now become more positive.
What is the reason for this change?
It's interesting because I think there are a couple of songs on the new album that may seem lighter, but there are also songs, such as The End or Just Breathe that qualify as very dark songs although they may sound a little positive.
With both, when Ed played them to me, I cried when I heard them and they're deep dark songs.
I think when you grow up and there's some trauma in your life and you lose a relative or a friend, those things start to influence your art and your music and those two songs certainly represent that to me.
Also, I think you can be a happy person and still be able to make music that's dark.
Peru:
Fujimori is again admitted for medical examinations
Former president Alberto Fujimori was admitted Tuesday to a public hospital to be evaluated for the loss of muscle strength in his legs, his family doctor reported.
Fujimori, 72, serving a 25-year prison sentence for human rights violations committed during his government (1990-2000), suffers from several ailments, including a cancer in the language for which he has been operated four times and which is kept under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, told TV Channel N that Fujimori will be evaluated for three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases to determine the reason for the pain and loss of strength of his lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion Fujimori would be a candidate to obtain the benefit of the pardon for humanitarian reasons, however, said he does not want it because he is known to be innocent.
He was operated on four times of cancer to the tongue, he has a weight loss of 18 kilos which has been joined by other pathologies such as severe erosive gastritis, the cyst of the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and circulatory problems in the legs, the doctor listed.
Fujimori has been in custody since September 2007 in the National Directorate of Special Operations of the police.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 people at the hands of an army annihilation squad that he operated clandestinely in the early years of his government.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political ties
An official procession, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica, and composed of several ministers and businessmen, will begin a visit to Mexico this Tuesday in order to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican pair, Felipe Calderón, the highest point of an extensive agenda of meetings with political, commercial authorities and a meeting with the Uruguayan community living in Mexico, according to the agenda disseminated by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents, in the city of Guadalajara, will be "property for the exchange of information on all political matters between the two nations," according to the South American country's Presidency published on its website.
According to local media, Mujica would seek to get Calderón to support Uruguay in the incident with France that arose when French President Nicolas Sarkozy included the South American country on a list of tax havens, at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that remain tax havens, a statement that provoked the rejection of Uruguay and the call to consult its ambassador in the European country.
Mexico has been chairing the G20 since November, a group composed of the most powerful emerging and developed countries in the world, and has been in force with the South American country since January this year, an agreement to exchange tax information in order to avoid double taxation.
The Uruguayan government has tried in recent years to speed up the implementation of tax exchange agreements in order to get out of the "grey list" of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), made up of countries that did not implement all international standards of tax cooperation.
In the commercial sphere, Mexico and Uruguay have been in force since 2004 a Free Trade Agreement (FTA) that has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
The bigoted plumber passes the three dimensions with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought, untiringly, for 25 years to save Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but he has never done so in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he will fight for the love of the girl in stereoscopic technology.
The title, which reaches stores around the world this month, has been designed from the beginning to take advantage of the features of the Nintendo 3DS portable console, which allows you to play in three dimensions without using glasses.
"Mario is the character who has to say how stereoscopy without glasses should work," said Nintendo's specialist press officer in Spain, Omar Álvarez, during the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Álvarez indicated that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first Nintendo video game originally designed for that support" , as so far successes such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" were adaptations of existing titles.
Nintendo spokesman has argued that, despite being in 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is an "accessible" video game that allows you to enjoy a fast and fluid game.
Álvarez has stated that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to engage less skilled users.
Once overcome, the most experienced will be able to give a "second lap" to the levels of play, which this time present greater difficulty.
In addition, users will be able to choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action, but it will be necessary to play in three dimensions in order to overcome the different challenges and "not succumb to optical illusions".
This incursion of Super Mario in all three dimensions also implies the character's return to a portable console, a fact that did not occur since 2005.
In this video game Nintendo winks at the followers of the saga and repeats the formula of the success of the previous installments, consisting of the mustache plumber having to tour platforms mined from dangers with the aim of releasing Princess Peach.
Although the player will find novelties in movements, environments, costumes and enemies and also a "playable" Luigi.
Colom endorses Portillo's extradition to the United States
President Álvaro Colom announced Tuesday that he processed the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to answer in the United States for the conspiracy to launder US$70 million.
Thus ends the process for Guatemala to respond to the request of the country of the north that demanded Portillo to judge him there.
In a press conference, Colom stated that his decision was based on the independence of the judiciary and the executive, taking into account that an extradition order had already been issued by a sentencing court.
He claimed that during his term he "did not put his hands" in court decisions and processed all the extraditions he has known.
In addition to Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will be extradited for murder and serious injuries, and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
What Colom has done is an executive procedure after all the judicial and constitutional bodies have been exhausted in order to prosecute the ex-mandatario from 2000 to 2004.
According to decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court (CC), Portillo must be extradited once his legal situation in Guatemala has been resolved and his human rights guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted for the embezzlement of Q120 million in the Ministry of Defence when he was president, which was the process that preceded extradition, but the Public Prosecutor's Office appealed and reactivated the case.
Trinijove has helped 6,000 youth at risk
The entity was born to avoid the fall in the marginality of boys without training
The balance sheet of the first 25 years of life of the social support organization Trinijove is important: 6,000 young people at risk of exclusion have been helped to overcome a difficult situation throughout this quarter of a century.
To this is added the 100 long jobs currently achieved for this social group.
The anniversary served yesterday to take stock in an event held in the former Fabra i Coats manufacturing complex attended by more than 300 people.
Trinijove was born in the Trinitat Vella neighborhood in 1986 with the aim of helping young people with little training, without work, with problems of dogradition or in a position to fall into marginality.
Yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu focused on a large number of heads of entities and institutions who in these 25 years have collaborated with the association.
The varied political representation, in full electoral time, showed the unitary character of the work carried out by Trinijove.
Together with the president of the Generalitat, Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, former socialist education advisor Ernest Maragall and former mayor and current ecosocialist councillor Ricard Gomà attended the event.
The current councillor of Benestar Social i Família, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the general director of the social work of La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa, also attended the grand hall of Fabra i Coats.
But he said that Trinijove was born in a very difficult time and that the current one is also, but added that the work done so far "is a good basis".
The president set Trinijove as an example for being able to fight bad circumstances and for giving hope to people in difficulty.
"The crisis is not something new for the entity and for the work it does," he said.
Evicted an okupada farm where they made macro parties
The invaders had taken over 11 of the 13 floors of the building, in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the farm yesterday noon without offering resistance
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare lived by the neighbors of 51 Balmes Street has come to an end.
Twelve people left yesterday's noon voluntarily the property they occupied illegally, and where they organized macro-fests that despaired the neighborhood, by court order and without the need for police intervention.
When the operation ended, the door lock was changed to prevent the situation from recurring.
"From now on there will be an access control," said the administrator.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building - the rest are inhabited-, took the entire electrical facility and part of the water, as well as painting the walls and leaving waste of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three floors were the scene of the mass parties, which lasted for up to two days and despaired the tenants.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which has also been damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat explained to Europa Press that since the building was occupied the business has fallen by 80%.
The owner of the club points out that the invaders of the estate made unfair competition, as they sold the drinks at three euros, while in the disco they were worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment venue had had to respond to neighborhood complaints of noise, while, according to him, the inconveniences are not caused by the clients of the discotheque, but by the inhabitants of the okupada house and, above all, those attending the parties that were organized there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to the angry neighbors of the area.
The manager of the disco explained that the inconveniences were so great that she even reached an agreement with the owner of the property and nine months ago she "forgave" him the rent.
The Urban Guard also confirmed that over the past few weeks it had received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
The president of the municipal PP group in the town hall, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had last week called for "immediately dislodging the building to end the problems of coexistence and citizenship that produce the neighbors, as well as the degradation of the area".
The popular leader explained that before the summer there was only one floor of the occupied building, but over the last few months the squatters had been entering all the floors of the building and almost all the floors, and that in some there have even been robberies.
In this sense he added that, "it is necessary to end impunity and be forceful against the incivism that has been generated on the estate."
Also yesterday, the Mossos evicted a building in Nou Barris.
At 3.30 p.m. the police proceeded to 35 Mont-ral Street, after receiving a call from a neighbour who had observed four people accessing the building.
All four were arrested at the time.
Park or mountain?
The architects agree on the opportunity of the call beyond polemics on fees
The municipal competition on the 16 doors reopens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now extinct Barcelona Metropolitan Corporation (CMB), this administration printed some promotional packages for Collserola.
The brochure defined the mountain as the great park of metropolitan Barcelona.
Moreover, it was accompanied by a comparison, in figures, with New York Central Park.
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park was once again placed, in the imagination of many, as the upper limit of Barcelona, being the Catalan capital of the few that are not oriented on the north-south axis but above (mountain) -below (sea).
Collserola's rating as a natural park results in this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with the wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
In these were until, in September, the city council convened a megacompetition composed of 16 contests for so many other doors of access to Collserola.
A door refers to the idea of a park, no doubt.
Either that or someone's trying to put doors in the field.
The question goes out alone: Collserola, park or mountain?
The competition, both because of its purely organizational aspect and because of what supposes of reflection on the city is the topic of conversation among all the Barcelona architects.
It is almost a recurring theme to be touched upon when two members of this former caste of elect are recognized in an elevator.
And this fact gives rise, precisely, to one of the few coincidences between what three Barcelona architects think, and university professors, who have presented themselves.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Mòdol and Marta Bayona: the contest is timely.
For Roldán, after addressing the coastal front "it becomes necessary" to debate about "the mountain front", since the discourse of Ildefons Cerdà, that of green apples, has not been carried out.
"It is possible to start from the base that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things because of its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex," says the architect for whom the title of "Door of Collserola" contains a "lexical trap": they should not be thought of "as the accesses to a park, but the delimitation of some areas where you have to act".
Mòdol, as Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, describes the proposal as "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
Dangers derived from the "uncertainness that it is today to project the public space" after the experience lived in the 80s and that he had in the area of the Forum "his singing of the swan".
The first fear is the very delimitation of borders on where it can be built.
"Limiting something is already setting the next step," i.e., its overstep.
"We have to think about new urban planning instruments, because the current ones [referring to the Metropolitan General Plan (PMM)] can give rise to real disasters."
Closer to the question, Mòdol believes that, simplifying, the valley slope of Collserola "can be understood as a park, that of Barcelona, not", by a purely topographical question.
Mòdol recalls that there is already a work done by the Patronat de Collserola that "must not fall into a broken sack", although he appreciates the opportunity that the council offers its union to intervene in this project "from the first moment".
And even more, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the safe conduct that allows the architects to enter into the debate, but "doubts" about whether it is this technical profile that should lead the multidisciplinary teams ("a great success", he points out) that they have had to create: "Architects should be only a tool".
Bayona insinuates that the answer to the question that gives title to this piece is complex, because in the bases of the contest lacks a global vision of Collserola: "There have been convened 16 transversal contests -he says- in the sense mountain-sea, but there is no longitudinal reading, that sees and understands the area as a whole".
This means, at least where appropriate, that it has chosen to take part in the 16 competitions.
Otherwise, a project for one of the doors can collide in program and definition with that of the architect next door.
In his view, however, the City Council should ensure that the strip immediately above the Dalt Round should provide, to its full extent, for an area of equipment that would make a smooth transition between the city and the green.
Casino forgives Jonah Larrazábal and will go free
After 72 days of taking root, the legal representative of Casino Red granted the pardon to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey of the process that followed him for alleged blackmail
After 72 days in prison, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the legal representative of Casino Red granted him the pardon before the Second District Criminal Court, which follows a blackmail trial against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the attack on Casino Royale, the owner of Casino Red, Sergio Gil García, made public a series of photographs and videos in which Manuel Jonah allegedly demanded that he pay an economic fee so that the regional council would allow the clandestine operation of the gambling house.
Following the public complaint, the State Attorney's Office opened criminal proceedings against the brother of the PAN mayor and on September 2 he was arrested and ingrained for 30 days.
After four hours before the Public Prosecutor's Office Agent 3 in Patrimonial Crimes, he was transferred to Arraigo House 1, located in the Old Quarter of the state capital.
He remained there for the 49 days following the issuance of a second rooting order after the Public Prosecutor ' s Office dismissed the crimes of bribery and organized crime.
On 19 October, he was transferred to Cadereyta prison for allegedly blackmailing the owners of Casino Red with 1.5 million pesos; however, he remained only for a few hours in the medium-security prison as there were death threats against him.
The authorities allowed him to follow the trial in the municipal cells of San Nicolás de los Garza.
On October 25, he was given an arrest warrant by the secretary of the Second District Criminal Court, Jorge Yanez, who said that almost two months after investigations, sufficient evidence was verified to determine Jonah's guilt, such as the collection of 1.5 million pesos from the representatives of the gambling house in exchange for allowing the operation of the latter.
On Monday, the legal representative of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, went to judge José Luis Pecina to ask for forgiveness for the brother of the royal mayor; so in the next few hours he could regain his freedom.
During the legal process, the Public Prosecutor's Office officer attached to the court, Ramiro Arias, questioned García Gómez if the damage had been repaired and who of the gambling associates was the one who granted the pardon, although the lawyer tried to reserve the name.
On the basis of the 197/2011 file, Jonás Larrazábal is granted a legal pardon and no complaint may be filed in connection with the proceedings that followed him, in addition to the fact that he will not be required to make reparation for damage or punishment.
Following the hearing of the legal representative of the gambling house, around 15:50 the immediate release of Larrazabal Bretón was ordered.
The court clerk, Jorge Yánez, moved to the prison in the municipality of San Nicolás de los Garza to notify Jonah that he has been legally pardoned and his file will be filed.
He will also notify you of the immediate release order issued by the judge.
Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives details of the plane crash where the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake, and seven other people lost their lives
The Ministry of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results released on the accident where the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people lost their lives, indicate that the helicopter was directly impacted on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to attempt a forced landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Pérez Jácome, Secretary of Communications and Transport, mentioned that before taking off the aircraft, the pilot found that the weather conditions were adequate to fly.
"The elements that seem to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the ground, the blades had contact with trees at 25 meters where the unit lost the fuselage".
He also reported that the unit was designed for 19 people, so he had the necessary requirements to transport the personnel.
In addition, he said that research done in the impact area does not report the appearance of pieces on the ground.
"In a search it is reported that there are no pieces or components of the ship elsewhere, the impact was presented structurally.
"The helicopter's design was for 19 passengers, it had adequate requirements to transport passengers.
The terrain presents a slope of seven degrees at 30 degrees of inclination.
For the time being, the secretary assured that it is a priority to have the results before possible; however, the research may last several months, it could even reach one year.
For his part, Gilberto López Meyer, general director of Airports and Auxiliary Services, said that at the time of the impact, the helicopter of the Presidential General Staff operated in cruising speed and that this happened in an ascending soft terrain.
"This information strengthens the hypothesis of a normal cruise operation at the time of impact," he said.
At the press conference, SCT headline Pérez Jácome listed six relevant elements in the investigation:
Visual flight:
According to the aeronautical regulations the flight was carried out under the visual flight rules, this implies that the crew must have visibility during the flight and the terrain.
Weather conditions:
Reports at the AICM placed conditions suitable for take-off, as the aircraft progressed towards the border area between the DF and the State of Mexico, layers of cloudiness were present at low altitude.
Selected paths:
It is likely that due to cloudy conditions the crew have sought an area of lower elevation and greater visibility towards the Cuernavaca valley.
Impact location.
The impact coordinates and the last record of the radar aircraft match, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersion of aircraft debris in a reduced area:
The information available so far suggests that the impact occurred on a straight and side path.
The aircraft ' s pattern of debris dispersion suggests that the helicopter was impacted on the ground in conditions of structural integrity.
No evidence of fire or explosion has been detected:
At the site of the accident, no evidence remains to be revealed in the ship's remains of any kind of explosion or fire.
The latest results of the investigation indicate that he may have had multiple contacts with the field.
During the field work, parts of the aircraft have been found at an elevation of 9,200 feet above the average sea level, the terrain presents a slope ranging from seven degrees to 30 degrees of inclination.
The photographs show the sequence in which he presumably disarticulated along the route.
The information provides elements that appear to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impacts on the ground.
After the thorough search in a wider area than the cordoned site, around the accident, no scattered parts of the aircraft have been found, which reinforces the presumption that the impact was presented under conditions of structural integrity.
MSS Announces Protocol to Find Obesity Gene
Social Security directs research to discover the obesity gene in children and young people; it is supported by IPN specialists
The Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS) announced that it is conducting research to discover the obesity gene in children and young people, called the 'Genetics of Childhood Obesity and Adolescence' protocol, which will allow for markers associated with overweight.
In a statement, Miguel Cruz López, head of the Medical Research Unit in Biochemistry at the Hospital de Especialidades del Centro Médico Nacional Siglo XXI, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers was integrated.
This team is supported by specialists and graduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Centre for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
In the research, the population is invited to participate, whether they are entitled or not, to go to the participating sports units of the IMSS in the Valley of Mexico, where the tests are carried out for minors, every Saturday from 8:00 a.m.
He stressed that the protocol began in the Quauhtémoc Sports Unit (State of West Mexico) and that since October 8, the activity has been carried out in the Nezahualcoyolt Sports Unit (State of East Mexico).
Once the goal of bringing together 500 or 600 minors is met, the study will continue in the Independence Sports Unit (southern Federal District) and finally in the Morelos Sports Unit (north Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research is to know the components and importance of genetics with respect to the development of obesity and to identify risk factors in Mexican children and young people to prevent the emergence of chronic degenerative diseases.
On November 14, World Diabetes Day, he said that the goal is to bring together 3,000 children and young people between the ages of six and 14 years, with the consent and supervision of their parents, for the application of specific food questionnaires.
They will also be asked about physical activity and family history of diseases, in order to avoid risk factors that trigger conditions such as diabetes or kidney failure.
He explained that on Saturdays anthropometric measurements (weight, size, waist circumference), blood pressure intake, determination of glucose, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin and genetic levels are applied to all participants (we seek to identify genes associated with childhood obesity).
Cruz López noted that this research is due to the concern of health professionals about the alarming weight gain in minors.
'The health surveys of 1999 and 2006 indicated that in just six years there was an increase, in the case of boys, of 77 percent in obesity, and of girls of 47 percent; in terms of overweight there was also a dramatic rise,' noted the specialist of the IMSS.
He indicated that the justification for the search for markers is based on the fact that the population of the country differs from others because of its genetic history.
He reported that on average, Mexicans have 65 percent of American Indian heritage, 30 percent European and five percent African and this condition is reflected in genes associated with diabetes and excess weight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity translates into the inability to burn the excess energy we consume (calories) that is stored in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit to the participants is the comprehensive evaluation of the children, which allows to detect if they have any degree of overweight or obesity.
Even, he said, the presence of dark-colored folds (acanthosis) in the neck and forearm, which indicate the likelihood of metabolic alterations and even prediabetes.
The information is handled confidentially, doctors hand it over in writing to parents, who are explained to each of the measurements and lifestyle changes they must make to prevent diseases.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: sedentarism, which is the lack of daily physical activity, staying most of the day sitting in front of the TV and using means of transportation instead of walking short distances.
It is also due to the high caloric intake, i.e. the higher consumption of sugary drinks, carbohydrates (tamals, bread, pizza, hamburger, etc.) with high fat and protein content and the genetics analyzed in this protocol.
Asphalt of UNAM would avoid potholes
Rafael Herrera, researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry at UNAM, develops asphalt modified with polymers to produce a mixture with better performance, regardless of environmental and temperature conditions
If the signals sent by the pavement were met, it would not be necessary to repair nearly 200,000 potholes each rainy season in the Metropolitan Zone of the Valley of Mexico, warned Rafael Herrera Nájera, researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of UNAM, who assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of an asphalt pavement is the right one, the potholes could be reduced in quantity or even eliminated completely.
In his lecture A technological opinion of potholes, given in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, announced that the laboratory in charge develops asphalt modified with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of asphalt, but with greater mechanical resistance, both at high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera estimated that this type of modified asphalt could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, like some cities in the north of the country, to improve their performance and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
He explained that asphalt, the heaviest part of oil, is a set of hydrocarbons molecules, some of high molecular weight, called asphaltenes, and others of low molecular weight, called Maltese, which together give the pavement its characteristic viscoelastic behavior.
The viscoelastic behavior of the asphalt consists in that at high temperatures, about 180 degrees, it behaves like a liquid, at 120 degrees Celsius its viscosity is very high and at 50 degrees Celsius it has an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes brittle, he added.
This means that in the streets the asphalt resistance is not uniform, but is modified during the day according to the environmental and temperature conditions, warned the specialist in chemical engineering.
The FQ researcher observed that the streets of Mexico City are mostly covered by flexible pavement, which consists of six layers of materials, of which the last three involve asphalt.
Among the most superficial layers is the asphalt folder, made up of small stones bathed in asphalt and then compacted.
Each of the pebbles that constitutes the folder, he pointed out, is bathed with asphalt.
When passing the vehicles and generating efforts, this allows the forces to spread very well on the pavement.
If it were modified asphalt they would spread even better, the chemical engineer said.
On the asphalt folder, he abounded, he placed a last layer called a rolling folder, which is made of a fine stone material, that is, a sand that is also bathed in asphalt.
As it is the layer that will be in contact with the tires of the vehicles, it should have more mechanical strength than the asphalt folder and provide friction on the way.
Being the part of the pavement that will receive and spread the efforts, the rolling folder also requires to have the appropriate thickness and should take care of the material from which it is made.
Climate, especially humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he said, because it significantly affects the performance of the asphalt folder.
When the soil moistens, the water diffuses inside the folder and it is difficult to leave, this causes a softening of all layers of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
In the process of forming a pothole, he said, the first to wear out is the bearing film and only after the asphalt folder is affected, but the damage does not occur instantly, but it is a process that should be attended to the first signals with proper maintenance programs.
